task_description: Facing the building to your South-West (approx. 220°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: I need to see the top of the building to estimate its height, so I will tilt my view upwards.
I can now see the top and bottom of the building; assuming each of the 6 visible floors is about 3.5 meters high, the total height is approximately 21 meters.
